In this 1.0.31 version of this script that uses the NewsGrabber.pm
Perl module. This package includes

* 1 perl script newsgrabber.pl
* 1 "update.txt" file
* 31 ".out" files
* 4 HTML template file
* This README file

To use the newsgrabber.pl script, you need to have the NewsGrabber.pm
module installed and the ability to run CGI scripts.

Using the script
----------------
1. Download this .tar.gz file into the cgi-bin dir. of your server. 
2. Gunzip and Tar-xvf the file.
3. chmod the newsgrabber.pl script to 755
4. chmod the *.out files to 777
5. chmod the update.txt file to 777
6. chmod the .template files to 644
7. Find out the directory in which the NewsGrabber.pm module is.
   Let me call it /home/abc/modules/NewsGrabber
8. Open newsgrabber.pl for editing using vi/pico/emacs etc.
9. Change the first line of the script to point to location of Perl
10.Fill in the "use lib 'FILL_ME!!!' " line with the path found in 7.
11.Enjoy. In case of doubts/bugs, pester me at srijith@srijith.net


